.TH "devm_rproc_add" 9 "devm_rproc_add" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_rproc_add \- resource managed rproc_add()
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" devm_rproc_add
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct rproc *rproc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the underlying device
.IP "rproc" 12
the remote processor handle to register
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function performs like \fBrproc_add\fP but the registered rproc device will
automatically be removed on driver detach.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, negative errno on failure
